sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: MTS
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Mitochondrial targeting sequence for Aspergillus nidulans
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Mitochondrial targeting sequence (MTS) for Aspergillus nidulans. A MTS is usually required for the entry of proteins and intermediary metabolites into mitochondria. The MTS is a DNA fragment encoding the N-terminal 60 amino acids of the AcuJ.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: DTU-Denmark-2
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Compatible with the Plug'n'Play assembly standard. This MTS should be placed at the N-terminal of the gene of interest.
